Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as bd1299b74c25fa6123cab497d4b8370689a7a999

Fix your commit message formatting (That's probably what CI is complaining about).

Leave a newline between your first line and paragraph description.  Tab in your list.  Ideally it would be a paragraph instead of a bulletted list.

Also try to cover "Why" you're doing this.  Most of what's above I can read from the commit contents.  Why is splitting this up and making it dynamic useful?
Acknowledged

I think this goes away now.  This file is now completely generated from meson.

This probably made sense a few months ago.
The alternative is to use BMCWEB_LOGGING_LEVEL directly in logging.hpp as it needs an anchor for loglevel for the first time
Yep, I think you got it.
Acknowledged
weird the CLI daemon needs http included.... but idk, we must have an include dependency there that doesn't make sense.
No need to fix anything, just weird.
Done
bmcweb doesn't need cli11 (yet)
Acknowledged
nit, can we call this "daemon" just be be more clear.
Acknowledged
can we call this "CLI application" instead of executable?
Acknowledged
I don't see iostream used?
Acknowledged

Acknowledged
needs clang formatted.
Acknowledged
You probably didn't intend to do this.
Done
Would it be better to add an example setLogLevel dbus command here?
Done
Leaving in review for a couple of days to see if anyone has comments, but LGTM.

It would better to update https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/DEVELOPING.md#enabling-logging section to show how the logging level can be controlled.

Should need another openbmc commit to add  dependency of `cli11` in `meta-phosphor/recipes-phosphor/interfaces/bmcweb_git.bb` ?
Yes, we'll need to add the dependency to the recipe.  We'll do that when we do the bump.
Added usage to DEVELOPING.md
Nit, trailing whitespace.
Done

I think this cli `bmcweb` is doing 
```
busctl call  xyz.openbmc_project.bmcweb /xyz/openbmc_project/bmcweb  xyz.openbmc_project.bmcweb SetLogLevel s "INFO"
```

I think it may be better to show the raw dbus busctl command example here & DEVELOPING.md.
I disagree.  The CLI commands are simpler to read and execute, and can encapsulate any DBus API changes we make.
Added busctl documentation in addition to CLI example
Sorry, but please remove the busctl docs.  I don't want to document an internal, should only be used from CLI interface.  That implies that other apps can use it, which they shouldn't be.
Done, removed
Given the scope of goal, it would be good to keep the CLI

Do we need still a separate cli bmcweb when it can be done via busctl (or dbus api)?

This would help for the others who may want to integrate directly using DBUS interface to control bmcweb log level.

If so, `cli11` dependency can also be removed.

How about dealing with `/tmp/bmcweb` (in TESTING.md)?
If `bmcwebd` needs to be used, TESTING.md would need to be updated.

On the other hand, if keeping `bmcweb` as is (instead of changing it to `bmcwebd`) and removing cli `bmcweb`, TESTING.md would not need to be modified.
We don't "need" any of this.  We could remove all logging alltogether.  We add things like this because it makes things easier.

I would prefer that the CLI application be called "bmcweb".

It's rare that people are launching bmcwebd directly (that documentation is the only case I'm aware of where it's expected, and that's a dev mode).

The CLI is useful for apps that need to turn on bmcweb logging during specific events, without inheriting sdbus dependencies -> effort towards a more generalized server. 
Also simplifies development when there's a need to alternate between logging levels.
Updated TESTING.md
If it is preferred to have a CLI cmd, what if naming it as "bmcwebctl" or "bmcwebcli"?
I prefer the current name.
Acknowledged
Given the scope of goal, it would agree
Since logLevel can be dynamically changed, I think it is better to add a trace line here saying the log level is changing.

I think we would need to handle the error case as the invalid loglevel may be passed (unlike the case when it was only controlled via compile time option).

For example,

```
busctl call  xyz.openbmc_project.bmcweb /xyz/openbmc_project/bmcweb  xyz.openbmc_project.bmcweb SetLogLevel s "INVALID"
```
I could see it being needed, although this is a CLI application for debug.  I'm not sure how far we really need to go on input validation.  Up to author if they want to fix.
Added a trace: Note, this is printed at an "INFO" level.
This error case is handled same as before - getLogLevelFromName(logLevel) returns disabled when invalid arg is passed.
Right, but ideally it would return an error to the CLI.  I'm not THAT worried about it, and I suspect it's something that can be fixed in a later patch.

Today code (`getLogLevelFromName()`) will set the log level as "Disabled" if the input is invalid.

So, I think `getLogLevelFromName()` needs to be modified to detect the invalid input and not to change the current log level as Disabled.

Like I said, yes, that would return an error, and you're right, that could be improved, but given this is a debug interface, and not user facing, I will leave up to the author if they want to spend the effort to fix that.

Agree. I would prefer if there's a single source of truth for the logging states, so I added a validation check in bmcwebd. If validation fails, we don't change log level:
root@s7106:~# journalctl -u bmcweb
Feb 27 17:26:38 s7106 systemd[1]: Started Start bmcwebd server.
Feb 27 17:27:01 s7106 bmcwebd[214]: [ERROR event_service_manager.hpp:1303] inotify_add_watch failed for redfish log file.
Feb 27 17:27:42 s7106 bmcwebd[214]: [INFO webserver_run.cpp:39] Requested log-level change to: DEBUG
Feb 27 17:27:52 s7106 bmcwebd[214]: [INFO webserver_run.cpp:39] Requested log-level change to: INFO
Feb 27 17:28:01 s7106 bmcwebd[214]: [ERROR webserver_run.cpp:35] log-level WRONG_INP not found
It seems good
It seems better
Given the scope of the goal, it looks good to me
